senna is a 2010 british documentary film that depicts the life and death of brazilian motor-racing champion ayrton senna , directed by asif kapadia . the film was produced by studiocanal , working title films , and midfield films , and was distributed by the parent company of the latter two production companies , universal pictures . the film 's narrative focuses on senna 's racing career in formula one , from his debut in the 1984 brazilian grand prix to his death in an accident at the 1994 san marino grand prix , with particular emphasis on his rivalry with fellow driver alain prost . it relies primarily on archive racetrack footage and home video clips provided by the senna family , rather than retrospective video interviews , and has no formal commentary .